startGuidance.heading = Calculate Stamp Duty Land Tax (SDLT)
startGuidance.content.l1 = This calculator can be used for property purchases that are:
startGuidance.bullet.b1 = for first-time buyers
startGuidance.bullet.b2 = replacing main residence
startGuidance.bullet.b3 = additional property
startGuidance.bullet.b4 = residential or non-residential
startGuidance.bullet.b5 = freehold or leasehold
startGuidance.bullet.b6 = for non-UK residents purchasing residential property
startGuidance.content.l2 = The calculator will work out the SDLT payable for most transactions. You should
startGuidance.content.l3 = if you are uncertain about how SDLT applies to your purchase or if you believe it may qualify for a relief.
startGuidance.content.l4 = There are
startGuidance.content.l5 = purchasing residential property for more than £500,000.


tenancy.heading = Is your transaction Freehold or Leasehold?
tenancy.error.required = Select ''Freehold'' or ''Leasehold''
tenancy.hint = Choose ''Freehold'' if it’s a freehold transaction or you’re acquiring an existing lease. Choose ''Leasehold'' if it’s a new lease.

propertyType.heading = Is the transaction residential or non-residential?
propertyType.hint = If it's a mixed transaction, choose 'Non-residential'.
propertyType.Residential = Residential
propertyType.NonResidential = Non-Residential
propertyType.error.required = Select ''Residential'' or ''Non-residential''

effectiveDate.heading = Effective date of your transaction
effectiveDate.hint.h1 = This is usually the completion date.
effectiveDate.hint.h2 = For example, 31 3 2014.
date.day = Day
date.month = Month
date.year = Year
effectiveDate.error.required.all = You must complete the effective date field
effectiveDate.error.required.two = Effective Date must include {0} and {1}
effectiveDate.error.required = Effective Date must include {0}
effectiveDate.error.invalid = Please enter a valid date

nonUkResident.heading = Are any of the purchasers non-UK resident?
nonUkResident.details.title = What we mean by non-UK resident
nonUkResident.details.d1 = Non-UK resident as an individual
nonUkResident.details.d1.p1 = You are treated as non-UK resident for Stamp Duty Land Tax (SDLT) if you are not present in the UK for 183 days or more in the 12 months before the effective date of the purchase.
nonUkResident.details.d2 = Non-UK resident as a company
nonUkResident.details.d2.p1 = Corporate purchasers will be non-UK resident if they are not UK resident for Corporation Tax purposes on the purchase date.
nonUkResident.details.d2.p2 = Special rules apply for UK resident companies which are under the direct or indirect control of persons who are not resident in the UK.
nonUkResident.details.d2.p3 = Special rules also apply for trusts and settlements.
nonUkResident.error.required = You must complete the effective date field

isPurchaserIndividual.heading = Are you purchasing the property as an individual?
isPurchaserIndividual.hint = Choose ‘Yes’ if you’re buying on your own, or you’re married or in a civil partnership. Choose ‘No’ if you’re a company or trust.

isAdditionalProperty.heading = Will the purchase of the property result in owning two or more properties?

ownsOtherProperties.heading = Have you ever owned or part owned another property?
ownsOtherProperties.content = We only need to know about residential property, or property that has both residential and non-residential use. This includes freehold property, or leasehold property of at least 21 years. Select yes if you either:
ownsOtherProperties.bullet.b1 = bought a property
ownsOtherProperties.bullet.b2 = inherited a property
ownsOtherProperties.bullet.b3 = are a beneficiary of a trust that owns a property

replaceMainResidence.heading = Is the property being purchased replacing your main residence?
replaceMainResidence.hint = If your previous main residence has not yet been sold choose "No". A refund may be available if the previous main residence is sold within 3 years.

purchasePrice.heading = Enter the purchase price
purchasePrice.hint = This is the chargeable consideration.
purchasePrice.detail.title = Is your chargeable consideration less than £40,000?
purchasePrice.detail.content = If the purchase price is less than £40,000, you don't need to pay SDLT or file a return.

mainResidence.heading = Will this property be your main residence?
